@startuml
title Widget Update Traversal - Sequence View

skinparam ParticipantPadding 8

participant "UpdateModule" as UpdateModule
participant "Root Widget" as Root
participant "Parent Widget" as Parent
participant "Child Widget" as Child
participant "UpdateTick" as Tick
participant "Mouse" as Mouse
participant "Keyboard" as Keyboard

UpdateModule -> UpdateModule : compute UpdateTick
UpdateModule -> Root : update(tick)
Root -> Root : skip if inactive or blocked
Root -> Root : _onUpdate(tick)
Root -> Parent : update(tick)
Parent -> Parent : _onUpdate(tick)

alt child active
	Parent -> Child : update(tick)
	Child -> Child : _onUpdate(tick)
else child inactive
	Parent -> Child : skip subtree
end

UpdateModule -> Mouse : expose current state to widgets
UpdateModule -> Keyboard : expose current state to widgets

note bottom
Update traversal is separate from event dispatch. Input state
has already been updated by the mouse and keyboard modules.
end note

@enduml
